         <abstract>
            <p>
               Lists of individuals, sometimes independent from any other note or context, but with the word <foreign xml:lang="gez">wās</foreign>/<foreign xml:lang="gez">wāḥəs</foreign> used to describe their role. Sometimes a list of guarantors/witnesses may be included 
               in  an acquisition note; normally into a litigation/reconciliation record.
            </p>
            <p>Examples are:
               <list>
                  <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESdd019"/>, f. 1r: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዋና፡ አባ፡ ጽጌ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ዋሕስ፡ አባ፡ አሥራተ፡ ማርያም። ለሰሎሞን፡ ዋሕሱ፡ አባ፡ ጽጌ፡ አረጋዊ፡</foreign>;</p>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESsdsm002"/>, f. 149b: <foreign xml:lang="gez">የብርሸ፡ ዋኅስ፡ ንሻይ፡ መድኅን፡ ኽለቴ፡ ተጠለልፍዋል፡ የመረሳ፡ ዋስ፡ ዳስያ፡ ዓይኔ። የወ[ን]ድሙ፡ የሐጎስ፡ ዋስ፡ መረሳ፡ የተስፋይ፡ ዋስ፡ አቶ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት። የረዳ፡ ዋስ፡ ብሩ፡ ተስፋይ። የአቶ፡ ዳስታ፡ </foreign>;</p>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESsdm001"/>, f. 156v.</p>
                  </item>
               </list>
            </p>
